=== Signal Task ===
Each turn, you will observe a signal composed of three attributes:
- Color: [{{ colors_str }}]
- Shape: [{{ shapes_str }}]
- Number: [{{ numbers_str }}]

A hidden rule maps certain attribute values to the correct action.
Your goal is to infer the rule from feedback and choose the right action each turn.

Available actions: [{{ actions_str }}]

The hidden rule follows one of these formats:
{% if difficulty == "easy" %}
  "If <attribute> is <value> then <action>, otherwise <default_action>."
  (The rule depends on a single attribute.)
{% elif difficulty == "medium" %}
  "If <attribute> is <value> then <action>, otherwise <default_action>."
  (The rule depends on a single attribute.)
{% elif difficulty == "hard" %}
  "If <attr_1> is <val_1> AND <attr_2> is <val_2> then <action_A>; if only <attr_1> is <val_1> then <action_B>; otherwise <default_action>."
  (The rule depends on two attributes with partial-match branching.)
{% elif difficulty == "expert" %}
  "If your previous action was correct then <override_action>; otherwise follow this rule: If <attr_1> is <val_1> AND <attr_2> is <val_2> then <action_A>; if only <attr_1> is <val_1> then <action_B>; otherwise <default_action>."
  (The rule depends on two attributes, and your previous turn's correctness can override the action.)
{% endif %}
